# Example .gitignore for an R research project
# The point of this file: tell Git what to NEVER track.

# --- R session junk ---
.Rproj.user/
.Rhistory
.RData
.Ruserdata

# --- Secrets: API keys, tokens, credentials ---
# .Renviron often holds API keys. NEVER commit it to a public repo.
.Renviron
*.pem
*.key

# --- Data: keep raw & sensitive data out of version control ---
# Track your CODE, not your (potentially confidential) respondent data.
data/raw/
*.csv
*.rds
*.dta
*.sav
*.xlsx

# --- Large / generated outputs ---
*.log
figures/*.png
figures/*.pdf

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
